Onboarding an existing project to GitHub If the project is not yet initialized by git, do the following first
git init ; # then create a .gitignore file if needed git add . ; git status -u ; # will show you all the files to be committed. git commit -m &#34;init commit&#34; ; Then connect it to GitHub
git remote add origin git@github.com:davxiao/my-proj.git ; git branch --set-upstream-to=origin/master master ; git pull origin master --allow-unrelated-histories ; git push ;
